headline: Intel earnings, new-home sales, mortgage rates: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend host Josh Lipton outlines the top stories for investors to watch on Thursday, July 24. Fresh earnings will be posted in the morning from Honeywell (HON), Union Pacific (UNP), Blackstone (BX), and Keurig Dr. Pepper (KDP). In the afternoon, Intel (INTC) and Deckers (DECK) will report results. New-home sales data for June will be out in the morning. Economists are expecting an uptick to 650,000 from May's 623,000. Weekly mortgage rate data from Freddie Mac (FMCC) will be posted for the week starting July 17. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend here.

headline: MAINGEAR Drops Retro95: A 90s Throwback with 2025 Firepower
summary: MAINGEAR, the leader in premium-quality, high-performance gaming PCs, today announced Retro95, a limited-edition PC drop that brings back the unmistakable style of a '90s-era horizontal desktop, now supercharged with cutting-edge hardware. Built for gamers who remember LAN parties, floppy disks, dial-up, and CD-based drivers, Retro95 is a nostalgic love letter to the golden age of PC gaming, reimagined for today's most demanding titles.

headline: Intel's chip contracting plan in spotlight on earnings day
summary: (Reuters) -Faced with slumping quarterly sales and a burgeoning loss, Intel shareholders will want to know new CEO Lip Bu-Tan's plans for the chipmaker's nascent contract manufacturing business.  Intel is set to report its sixth consecutive net loss on Thursday, while revenue is expected to drop for a fifth straight quarter, according to estimates from LSEG data.  The storied chipmaker, once synonymous with America's chipmaking heft, has lagged due to years of strategic missteps.
